troduced to replace the DTD and to enable the creation of a data type that can process document more easilv Supporting data types: More complex types of data than the existing DTD can be created, and new types can be created and used. Supporting complex structure definition: Another schema document can be included in a schema document the Schema location directive: Supporting a namespace: XML Schema supports a namespace Namespace: An abstract entity that can distinguish elements when extracting elements from an XML document tvpe and combining them with other documents and when processing multiple documents at the same time using','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(494,'116','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',2,'67b50a3ed59a9.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3ed59a9.png','2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:26'),(495,'116','App\\Models\\Section','Text','XQuery is a query language that is used to search a XML-based database, and can extract information from XML files as if using a database:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(496,'117','App\\Models\\Section','Text','XLL is a standard language that performs link functions in an XML document, such as XML documents and setting specific locations within an XML document. XLL was introduced to overcome the limitations of HTML-based simple hyperlinks and to provide various approaches to using resources on the web XLL supports various hyperlink methods and two-way links between link resources XLL can use some of the required web resources by using XPointer or XPath, and is used as a core technology in X-Internet, etc, Supports two types, ie. Xpointer when moving within the same document, and Xlnik when moving between different pages, etc Provides a two-way link between resources Provides an extended pointer (XPointer) for resource locating: Linl tuno Cimnlo Fvtondod | ocator Groun Documant llinking','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(497,'118','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 17  Building a multimedia database',2,'67b50a3ee1d17.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3ee1d17.png','2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:26'),(498,'118','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The multimedia database was developed to efficiently search and manage unstructured multimedia data characterized by their large capacity and complexity, such as text, image, audio, video, etc. Existing databases face limitations due to the exponential increase of unstructured multimedia data, and an object-oriented approach,, the synchronized representation of multimedia, and the concept of time-dependent modeling were used to model various tvpes of unstructured data.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(499,'119','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Unlike general commercial databases in which a database is stored on a disk the main memory database manages and manipulates a database by keeping it in the memory: The current trend is that the main memory database is actively used due to business demands, such as securing the competitiveness of an enterprise through quick decision-making, and the revolutionary development of related technologies such as the release of 64-bit OS, the','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(500,'119','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Tcuuclon 0i Tctu } piiCcd, CLC The MMDB has the following characteristics due to the fact that the database runs in the main memory: Disk IO does not occur because all operations are performed in the main memory: Performance is good because disk IJO, which degrades performance in the disk-based database, is rare Hardware-based error recovery techniques are used due to the volatility of the main memory: A disk is used for backup and logging: Hashing and T-tree indexing algorithm optimized for a memory environment is used. Types of commercial main memory databases can be updated at [https:Ilen.wikipedia orghiki List_of_in-memor} databases]','',6,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(501,'120','App\\Models\\Section','Text','General commercial databases are not suitable for the embedded system, which has limited memory and special performance goals. The embedded database was developed for the embedded system, so as to allow specific functions to be used in a limited embedded environment Asa result, the embedded database has the following technical characteristics It provides essential functions only after reducing overheads to use minimum RAM and disk It supports communication between different devices to allow communication with the database in a central server It supports porting to the various platforms of the embedded system: It satisfies the performance requirements of the real-time OS of the embedded system: The list of commercial embedded databases can be updated at [http Ilembedded-databasescom','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(502,'121','App\\Models\\Section','Text','he mobile database is exclusively used by mobile devices The mobile database,, which is installed in a mobile device, rocesses the data generated field work ad sends them to the central server for synchronization Due to ne distinct characteristics of installation in a mobile device, mobile database should be independent from various latforms and operation systems, should recover quickly from failures, and should be optimized for a limited mobile during The mobile database is exclusively used by mobile devices: The mobile database, which is installed in a mobile device, processes the data generated field work ad sends them to the central server for synchronization Due to the distinct characteristics of installation in a mobile device, a mobile database should be independent from various platforms and operation systems, should recover quickly from failures, and should be optimized for a limited mobile environment As a result, the mobile database has the following characteristics. The database can be installed in a small capacity device equipped with a limited CPU and memory: It is provided as an embedded form that integrates data and applications It has the function of data replication and synchronization with the database of the existing server Commercial mobile databases include Sybase SQL Anywhere, Oracle Lite, Microsoft SQL Server Compact, SQLite, and IBM DB2 Everyplace during','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(503,'122','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A spatial database is a set of non-spatial data represented by letters and numbers and spatial data represented by coordinate values The spatial database was initially developed because a technology for processing unstructured data\" , such as the geographic information system was needed as a core technology for a type of guided missile that strikes a preset target by tracking the targets location using geographical information: Thereafter, the database was introduced full scale, as the market was expanded to include services that store and manage values for specific locations using geographical information,, such as GIS and location information check spatial','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(504,'122','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Geometry, a geographical object, and topology for the relationship between objects are included Unstructured data can be processed, large amounts of data can be processed quickly: Spatial (topological, geometric) characteristics are reflected New index and operation (R-tree index) are used to sort data that cannot be sorted Expressive data model that can express complex information Supports the combination of spatial data and non-spatial data spatial','',7,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(505,'123','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'',4,'67b50a3f049c1.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3f049c1.png','2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:27'),(506,'123','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A column base database physically stores data based on columns The data storage method of the relational database is not defined as row base or column base, but general relational databases use a physical storage structure based on rows However, a way to store data with this structure reached the limit in analyzing large-scale data at high because its physical structure required that unnecessary data should be also read The concept of column storage did not suddenly appear recently: Rather, this concept was studied relatively early on, including TAXIR which was developed in 1969 for searching biological information Recently, as the demand for the rapid processing of large amounts of data increased, a function that partially borrowed the concept of the column store such as the column store index, column store base DBMS, and hybrid DBMS supporting both structures were developed from the mid 2000s. Column base database technology is now actively used in the DBMS market, together with the main memory database The column base database has the following structure and characteristics compared to the row-based database speed being','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(507,'123','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The list of commercial column-oriented databases is updated at [https:Ilen wikipedia orglwiki/List_of_column oriented_DBMSes]:','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(508,'233','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Static structure requirements: Entity, property, relationship, constraint, etc Dynamic structure requirements: Transaction type, frequency, etc:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(509,'234','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Abstract conceptualization of the information structure appearing in the real world The entity, entity identifier relationship between entities, number and sequence of corresponding relationship entity properties, etc can be identified Generally represented by an entity-relationship (ER) model','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(510,'235','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Conversion of the result of the conceptual design, which is created for human understanding, into a logical structure that can be easily stored in a database There are the relational, network, hierarchical and object-oriented models, of which the relational model is most generally used. In case of the relational model, the table name, primary (PK), foreign (FK), etc. are determined in the logical design phase. A logical schema is created as a phase deliverable Normalization is performed according to the requirement level key key','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(511,'236','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Determination of the physical storage structure of the database created using logical structure design Definition of the data type of the column, constraints, and access method and for specific data. A technology for converting the structure according to the performance requirements is needed Specifically, transaction analysis,view design, index design, capacity design, and approach design are performed A physical schema is created as a phase deliverable. path','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(512,'125','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'<Table 19  Types of data modeling',2,'67b50a3f15135.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3f15135.png','2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:27'),(513,'125','App\\Models\\Section','Text','data model is a design document for building a database that has a clear goal. In the real world, a database created over time, as shown below: Depending on the level of abstraction, the design can be divided into a conceptuz data model, a logical data model, and physical data. From the real world to the database. Real world Conceptual world  Conceptual data modeling Entity Conceptual structure Logical data Physical (computer) world modeling Storage Physical data modeling Logical structure database First, conceptual data modeling is performed to embody the database at the higher level that has a high level of abstraction in the real world. The conceptual data model has a high level of abstraction, focuses on business, and performs modeling at the comprehensive level. This model is frequently used for enterprise data modeling ad EA establishment: For reference, when deploying EA-based enterprise data modeling: general data modeling, which is a higher level, is performed first, after which conceptual data modeling is performed for each business area. When a entity-centered data model is completed at the higher level, a data model with a focus on concrete business can be created according to a concrete business aspect and flow, which is called \"logical data modeling\". In addition, a method that considers the tablespace according to the storage structure of the database is called \"physical data modeling\".','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(514,'237','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Creation of a database that can accommodate the user requirements by writing and executing SQL statements needed to configure a database.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(515,'240','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','D Continuous maintenance and follow-up evaluation: Deliverables to be analyzed, design subject, impact of design.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(516,'241','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','The meaning of data and the rules of the correlation between data are defined in this phase A conceptual dat model should be created as a deliverable by defining the subject area, key entity and relationships in this phase','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(517,'242','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Attributes and should be defined based on the previously created conceptual data model, entities should be specified accordingly: and a final entity-relationship diagram should be created after defining history management keys','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(518,'243','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','physical schema is implemented in a physical data model to implement a database. Semi-normalization can be performed in consideration of performance in this phase. A table definition document reflecting these requirements is created','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(519,'129','App\\Models\\Section','Text','A data architect (DA) plays the most important role in the database design phase The data architect, who is directly involved from the phase of requirement collection, establishes a data management and defines the data standards In addition, the data architect manages the overall data models that are created by conceptual, logical, and physical modeling: However, the performance aspect should be considered in the physical modeling phase, to ensure that the database concerned will work well regardless of whether the user requirements are implemented. At this time, the database administrator (DBA) may review and reflect the physical structure area, such as the indexes partitions, as well as the clustering storage space, and denormalization That is, the data architect and the database administrator should discuss and determine the final physical model which as the best from their own perspectives in the physical modeling phase, so as to achieve efficient and stable performance system they - regard','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:05','2025-02-18 22:31:05'),(520,'130','App\\Models\\Section','Text','phase in which ambiguity is removed from the requirements by collecting and analyzing the busines: equirements. required specification (or job description) is produced as a deliverable','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:06','2025-02-18 22:31:06'),(521,'131','App\\Models\\Section','Text','sign in the order of conceptual modeling - logical modeling ~ physical modeling:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:06','2025-02-18 22:31:06'),(522,'244','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Conceptual modeling is the phase in which an ERD is produced, whereas logical modeling is the phase in which the structural drawing of the table is produced. These two phases are clearly separated Therefore, the entities and relationships of the ERD are identified in the conceptual modeling phase, and the primary and foreign of the table are identified in the logical modeling phase Normalization that handles table structure should be performed in the logical modeling phase For reference, \"physical modeling\" refers to the process of creating tables suitable for an actual DBMS. The Chen type of ERD is mainly used The relationship itself can have its own properties in the ERD. keys keys','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:06','2025-02-18 22:31:06'),(523,'245','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table 21  Differences in the understanding of data modeling',6,'67b50a3f20530.png','/storage/tables/67b50a3f20530.png','2025-02-18 22:31:06','2025-02-18 22:31:27'),(524,'245','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','An ERD is produced during logical modeling: Conceptual modeling further abstracts the ERD and summarizes it at a comprehensive level including the subjec area, core entity, core relationship, and core attribute: Conceptual modeling is not studied in the academic world The Crows Foot type of ERD is mainly used.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:06','2025-02-18 22:31:06'),(525,'245','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If the relationship has its own attributes, are included in the connected or included by identifying a relationship entity: For your reference, \"physical modeling\" refers to the process of converting an ERD into a table structure In general, normalization is performed in the logical data modeling phase, and denormalization is performed in the physical data modeling phase they entity','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:06','2025-02-18 22:31:06'),(526,'133','App\\Models\\Section','Text','\"Process modeling\" refers to the task of finding missing or unnecessary tasks to satisfy the functions required by the target system, by analyzing a given task efficiently within a specified period of time, When analyzing large and complex tasks In addition, it is regarded as most important to develop a high-quality system by classifying the analyzed tasks systematically and by designing the menu of the target system and program system. When a task is analyzed using & methodology, the task can be arranged systematically in order to find most of missing or unnecessary tasks, which is helpful when creating a data model The process hierarchy diagram is a frequently used process model, and the task process is subdivided into the function area, function, process, and unit process according to the size of the task','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:06','2025-02-18 22:31:06'),(527,'134','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Correlation modeling is a method of analyzing what is happening (process) to something (data) that exists within the task concerned and what is affected by which event, when developing an information system: Correlation modeling is performed by using the entity type identified from data modeling ad the unit process identified from process modeling: Whether or not data are generated by the entity type and the unit process can be verified using the CRUD matrix which enables the developer to verify the task for the data model and the process model in the analysis phase, and which can be used to understand the test and task data exchange in the future development phase','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:06','2025-02-18 22:31:06'),(528,'135','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The phase of abstractly conceptualizing and expressing the information structure appearing in the real world Conceptual modeling begins with analyzing and finding the data requirements of the organization and user, and includes the process of determining which data are important and t