transactions simultaneously? For example, what happens if you transfer KRW 1,000 online from an account with a balance of KRW 1,000 and withdraw KRW 1,000 from a ATM at the same time? In reality, it is naturally impossible, because the database system controls these transactions As explained so far the database system provides a concurrency control method to secure the isolation of a transaction, which ensures that the transaction is not affected by the change made by another transaction at the same time. However if the level of transaction isolation is high, simultaneous access to the database (concurrency) becomes difficult and performance is negatively affected. Therefore, the isolation level should be selected appropriately by considering the nature of the transaction In fact, service failure occurs frequently in the field due to the problem with concurrency control including the case of the college course registration crisis that occurred due to the application of the isolation level of the banking system, which requires strict transaction isolation, to the course registration system: Therefore, the concept of transaction and concurrency control should be correctly understood to determine the \"appropriate\" level of the to be developed and transaction isolation thing update college system','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:09','2025-02-18 22:31:09'),(792,'406','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','A transaction is a set of several operations constituting a logical task unit, which converts a consistent state of the database to another consistent state. A transaction is also a unit of performing a series of read and write operations in a database, which should be nerformed At the came time atabase to another consistent state','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-18 22:31:09','2025-02-18 22:31:09'),(793,'407','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 42] Conceptual diagram of a transaction',2,'67b50a4204820.png','/storage/figures/67b50a4204820.png','2025-02-18 22:31:09','