arning is the reason for the recent development of artificial intelligence: Deep learning is a branch of machine learning, and a method of solving problems similarly to how humans solve problems using an artificial neural network which performs the transfer ad processing of information with multiple nodes This method is based on human neural network theory: rapid','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2321,'919','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table85 Characteristics of Big Data',2,'67b65b95239af.png','/storage/tables/67b65b95239af.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2322,'919','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Trends\" is a quintessential Data service that was launched by Google for the general In 2008, Google hit upon the idea that people search for cold or flu on the Internet if suspect that have the flu, The company released a service that predicts cold and flu trends by analyzing the search information and the location of the people searching with keywords like \"flu\" and \"cold\" . Credit card companies are another group that rely big time on Big Data: analyze consumption and behavioral data of their customers and use it for marketing, product development, and product recommendation Big Data refers to data that is so large that it is difficult to handle them with traditional data storage, management, and analysis methods, are data whose size has exceeded the limits of what could be managed as a general database. Big Data is difficult to quantify through conventional methods because the 3Vs of volume, variety, and velocity are all large, and also include unstructured or non-metrical variables, making it difficult to analyze population trends or characteristics through statistical analysis. Big Data is often represented using visualization tools \"Flu \" Big public they they They they','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2323,'920','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',2,'67b65b9530000.png','/storage/figures/67b65b9530000.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2324,'920','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Fin Tech is a composite word created from \"Financial\" and \"Technology\" and refers to services like payments remittances, asset management, cloud funding, &nd loans, where traditional financial services are integrated with technologies Originally, it was the term used for describing a large vendor who develops services exclusively for financia= institutions, but it is now used to refer to the various services offered by financial startups Traditional financial institutions (usually the offline sales branches) have been able to secure security and reliability through powerful security system and database link to traditional institutions. In payment services, credit card companies have led the market by dominating the market early: However, some of the newer fintech firmsare able tc provide services based on smartphone-based mobile devices, financial management through Data analysis, anc credit risk assessment at significantly lower costs than existing financial institutions In payment services too, fintech companies are able to provide smart-phone services that are convenient and has great security of accessibility The growth of fintech services can be attributable to the following factors Big The popularization of mobile services, open source codes that can be developed and applied freely, the emergence of cloud technology ad the demand for new financial services from financial consumers have resulted in the growth of the startup scene Because fintech are Internet-based services, this means initial investment costs and labor costs can be very low_ So people feel little burden when investing in fintech development As consumers flock to mobile financial transactions that are faster ad cheaper than the financial services offered by existing banks, many companies are showing interest in fintech development: Fintech services could become a serious threat to traditional financial companies In payment and remittance, the ease of customer acquisition ad accessibility of services provided by the scalable platform will pose a threat In lending and investments, the high predictability provided by social data and Big Data will pose a threat: In particular, payment and remittance services are services that are frequently used and have strong platform characteristics For this reason, new companies like to use it as a stepping stone when starting other financial services In fact, Alibaba Orol iidec wariouc financial ceniices baced on Alinav A navment ceniice','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2325,'921','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Table87 Examples of 020 services',2,'67b65b953a6b7.png','/storage/tables/67b65b953a6b7.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2326,'921','App\\Models\\Subsection','Figures',NULL,'',4,'67b65b9547398.png','/storage/figures/67b65b9547398.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2327,'921','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','020 is the counterpart to the showrooming phenomenon where customers would first check the goods in offline stores such as marts and department stores and then pay for the same product in online space: In other words, describes the behavior of paying for goods online and receiving the good or service in offline space','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2328,'921','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','O4O(Online for Offline)','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2329,'921','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','040 means \"Online for Offline\" It means expanding the scope of business operations online to offline. An 040 service provider drives market innovation by operating an offline business by leveraging the value provided to its customers online: Amazon Go is a shocking example that illustrates the value and meaning of 040. Why did Amazon Go, an offline mart that sells simple groceries and miscellaneous goods send such shockwaves to the offline mart market? To use Amazon Go, customers must activate a mobile app and then log in. And then just have to bring their purchases out of the store Amazon Go automatically settles the bill through the customers account information and delivers the receipts to the customer Of course, customers must be registered with Amazon Prime before using Amazon Go. Customers don\'t have to wait in line at the counter to pay ad don\'t have to go through the process of putting the on the counter and packing them in a grocery This is a very clear-cut case 040 where an online company leverages their strengths for customer convenience from they goods bag','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2330,'922','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Comparison of virtual currency, cash and digital currency',4,'67b65b955b504.png','/storage/tables/67b65b955b504.png','2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:45'),(2331,'922','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','In recent years, interest in cryptocurrency has been hot due to the surge in the adoption of crypto currencies lik Bitcoin and Ethereum: While under the strict definition, it is correct to call Bitcoin and Ethereum cryptocurrencies, th term virtual currency is often used instead.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2332,'922','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Virtual currency or virtual money is defined as a digital currency or electronic currency used in electronic form in a virtual space on a network without any physical bill or coins According to the definition given by the European Central Bank (ECB), the U.S Treasury Department, and the European Bank Oversight Office, virtual currency is a type of digital currency that is issued and managed by developers and is not controlled by the government It used only in certain virtual communities as a form of payment and most crypto currencies can be seen as a digital currency and a virtual currency:','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2333,'922','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','urce: Kim seup, 2016, \"Current Status and Implications of Distributed Ledger Technology and Digital Currency , Bank of rea, results of payment survey: Dong = Reasons for the rise in the value of virtual currencies Most virtual currencies such as Bitcoin have fixed amount of final issuance, and if the method of block production through large scale calculations is maintained, scarcity is created by the consumption of physical resources for mining: In addition, virtual currencies produce a network effect that increases their value because are held simultaneously by multiple people The value of virtual currency increases due to scarcity and network effects However, the value of virtual currency cannot be explained just with its scarcity and network effect they Can it be said that the currency is the essence of virtual currency? The 3 important functions of currency are \"storage of value\', \"exchangeable\", and \"scale of value\". In the case of virtual currencies such as Bitcoin, the volatility is so severe that it cannot perform the \"scale of value\" function and thus it cannot be recognized as a true currency: The opinion of most experts is that virtual currency can never displace a nation\'s legal currency However, it has been verified by Ethereumthat a virtual currency can provide services beyond its use as a mode of payment. It should be noted that the increasing value of payments and other services of virtual currency can increase the price of virtual currency itself price Major virtual currencies More than 1,100 types of virtual currencies are currently listed and in use worldwide However, Bitcoin and Ethereum account for more than 70% of the value of virtual currency based on market capitalization.','',5,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-19 22:30:30','2025-02-19 22:30:30'),(2334,'923','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'<Ta