on material. Glancing over at the material while speaking may often make you look less confident because you do not make eye contact with the audience, which may undermine credibility in what you say, and make the presentation itself boring: Therefore, you should always be familiar with the order of the presentation material and maintain a natural flow so that you can continue your presentation even without reading the material. Appropriate and Interesting Opening Comments You should start your presentation with a story that can relate to topics such as simple weather, current status, and recent issues, and that can arouse the audience\'s interest If you go straight into the topic from the beginning, the atmosphere may become rigid and the relationship between the presenter and the audience may become awkward. It\'s okay to talk lightly, so prepare a comment that can help create a comfortable atmosphere of the first encounter with the audience Presentation Material Review Tcociucioi vulcniaiC Check the prepared presentation material for any errors. Since the style in which the prepared material is displayed may vary depending on the version or font of the presentation tool software, it is recommended to bring with a laptop, etc. to be ready for an unexpected situation: points of each sheet and appropriate examples to promote understanding Check the key points to be presented for each sheet once again, and whether the cases prepared to promote better understanding are well connected. It is also to make use of presentation tools or prepare a simple cue sheet Key good good Impressive closing comments At the end of the presentation, prepare a closing comment so that you can leave an impressive message to your audience. It is also to use aphorisms or quotes related to the contents of the presentation, or to convey impressively the words you saw in the book The important is that the closing comment is well linked to the subject so that the subject content can be more deeply relatable good good point','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2617,'1047','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Your appearance and image is also very important factor to win the audiences trust: In order to make a impression, you need to have a neat appearance, hairstyle, and attire. It is difficult to make a impression and look trustworthy when you look messy: And you should have a smiling face. If you are gloomy or stiff, you may present a negative image good good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2618,'1048','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','You must keep your eyes clear and bright: Insecure eye gaze cannot make you look confident or trustworthy: Eye contact is a very effective way to make a presentation successful. When giving a presentation, it is most important to make eye contact with the people who make decisions. Look at one person at a time, but distribute your visual attention about 60% to the decision maker and 40% to the rest of the audience It is necessary to observe the other person\'s reaction and develop a connection through contact\". key \"eye \"','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2619,'1049','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','You must explain with correct pronunciation and appropriate speed, and presenting with a resonant voice helps to enhance delivery: Rather than keeping the of voice constant,, you should immerse the audience by controlling the such as making it slow, fast, or a pause, etc speed speed','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2620,'1050','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Body language is effective to use when emphasizing important points. If you take too much exaggerated motion, you can make a negative impression. It s a idea to use the proper hand movements at the right timing: good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2621,'1051','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','If you emphasize something with your voice, and make a gesture afterwards, it may not be effective. It is effective to make a gesture at the same time or slightly ahead of an utterance. Make eye contact and use your hand gestures together while vocalizing as if pressing the voice slowly:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2622,'779','App\\Models\\Section','Figures',NULL,'[Figure 17]',2,'67b73d3ef007e.png','/storage/figures/67b73d3ef007e.png','2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:33:34'),(2623,'779','App\\Models\\Section','Text','According to The Law of Mehrabian, 93% of non-verbal body language such as gestures ad tone of voice is used to persuade the other person in actual communication The logical explanation occupies only 7%. Here, body language includes voice.','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2624,'779','App\\Models\\Section','Text','For example, we think that an actor with voice is at acting: No matter how well you act, if you cannot speak well, you may be seen as if you are not at acting How to effectively use body language in your presentation is as follows good good good','',3,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2625,'780','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Scenario is a kind of simulation of using a given time in a certain way: No matter how the presentatic material is, if you aren\'t prepared to when to throw a certain message, the presentation is highly likely to fail. Therefore, it is good to write a message to explain in a slide note and print it out for rehearsal. Rehearsal good to practice once or twice by imaging as if there is an audience to hear you: good','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2626,'781','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Tension is the greatest enemy of the presentation, and lowering tension is a very important factor in an actual presentation. An example of how to reduce tension before a presentation is below: presentation: An example Of how to reauce tension betore a presentation IS below: Clench and unclench your fist repetitively: Do a belly breathing: Repeat inhaling deeply and exhaling Go to the presentation venue early to ready: Do more rehearsals to enhance confidence. Having a chat with a colleague before the start can reduce the tension Encourage yourself by saying \"It\'s to make a mistake \" and \"Right nowl Im okay:\" in your mind long: get okay','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2627,'782','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Most novice presenters are not at first greeting: That\'s why you may feel nervous throughout the entire presentation, as if the first button was misplaced. For example, let\'s say you made your first greeting as fol lows. good Good morning: Im A from O0 department at O0 Company: (Greeting at the same time) Good morning:\" (Greeting), \"Im A from O0 department at O0 Company It\'s nice to see you, Which would be better? In the first case, there are too many words to say before bowing: The timing to make bow may not coincide with the applause of the audience: As in the second example, if you greet the audience with a short greeting message to the audience, and after receiving applause, look around and introduce yourself, you will be able to give a more relaxed presentation','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:16:47'),(2628,'783','App\\Models\\Section','Tables',NULL,'Table 29  Response of the presentation',2,'67b73d3f05099.png','/storage/tables/67b73d3f05099.png','2025-02-20 14:16:47','2025-02-20 14:33:35'),(2629,'783','App\\Models\\Section','Text','The presentation is present You make a connection with others and communicate with them, and the pur pose is to draw empathy and make the other person make decisions. You should be able to think about the voice tone, speed, content, emphasis, and story transition from various angles while monitoring the reaction of the other person. The positive and negative reactions of the audience are as follows','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 1