,'[Figure 36] Types of Functions',2,'67b73d41bf590.png','/storage/figures/67b73d41bf590.png','2025-02-20 14:16:48','2025-02-20 14:33:37'),(2752,'811','App\\Models\\Section','Text','Function Point is a method of estimating the cost by measuring the scale of software development as a Func- tion Point (FP) and multiplying the unit price per function It is an international standard (ISO/IEC 14143) that quantitatively calculates functions requested by and delivered to users from a user\'s of view, and is a cost calculation method for software development, maintenance and operation. Compared to the LOC (Line Of Code)-based COCOMO method or the ManjMonth (MM) method, it has the characteristic of grasping the size of the development project before initiation by identifying the required function of the user point point Software functions are divided into Data Functions and Transaction Functions, and more specifically, data functions are subdivided into Internal Logical Files and External Interface Files, and transaction functions are subdivided into three types: External Inputs, External Outputs, and External Inquiries','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:48','2025-02-20 14:16:48'),(2753,'1090','App\\Models\\Subsection','Tables',NULL,'',3,'67b73d41cdff1.png','/storage/tables/67b73d41cdff1.png','2025-02-20 14:16:48','2025-02-20 14:33:37'),(2754,'1090','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','When the required labor is allocated for each work package, the unit price per labor must be determined In the case of Korea, the average wage of a software engineer published by Korea Software Industry Association is applied, which is determined by referring to the table below:','',1,NULL,NULL,'2025-02-20 14:16:48','2025-02-20 14:16:48'),(2755,'1091','App\\Models\\Subsection','Text','Overhead cost is indirect expenses incurred in the areas of planning, management, and general affairs for the administrative operation of the software developer Usually, it is calculated as 110 to 120% of the direct l