 scope requirements.\"','[\"Reevaluate the budget based on new scope requirements.\", \"Ignore the budget and continue with the project.\", \"Only report the changes to the team.\", \"Maintain the original budget regardless of changes.\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2863,6,'Test','How does the concept of cost estimation differ between public and private projects? Compare the methodologies used and analyze how these differences impact the overall project budgeting process.',0.8,1.7,'Hard','C6-rnG5VumHQ+6F8xgMn7Mqpg','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Public projects focus on user functional requirements\", \"Private projects may use more flexible estimation methods\"]','[\"Public projects focus on user functional requirements\", \"Private projects may use more flexible estimation methods\", \"Both projects use identical estimation processes\", \"Public projects do not require cost estimation\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2864,6,'Test','When applying the Function Point Analysis (FPA) method, what are the critical components that must be measured to estimate software development costs? Distinguish between data functions and transaction functions and analyze their contributions to the overall cost estimation.',0.8,1.4,'Hard','C6-sx7OQBQhRlSGyTgzgQvjMg','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Data functions\", \"Transaction functions\"]','[\"Data functions\", \"Transaction functions\", \"Only data functions matter\", \"Transaction functions are irrelevant\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2865,6,'Test','When managing project costs, how does effective communication with stakeholders influence cost management practices? Analyze the relationships between stakeholder engagement and successful cost control measures.',0.8,1.2,'Hard','C6-oIccZvtBQ7ubapnfbVbM7A','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Effective communication fosters transparency and accountability.\"','[\"Effective communication fosters transparency and accountability.\", \"Stakeholder engagement is unnecessary for cost management.\", \"Only the project manager needs to communicate.\", \"Cost management can be done without stakeholder input.\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2866,6,'Test','In the context of business communication, identify and differentiate between the key elements involved in the process of sharing information. Consider the roles of the sender, receiver, medium, and the encoding and decoding processes. How do these elements interact to minimize noise and ensure effective communication?',0.8,1.4,'Hard','C6-bARQGwmmQu6801QEuD2ISw','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Sender, Receiver, Medium\"','[\"Sender, Receiver, Medium\", \"Sender, Message, Feedback\", \"Medium, Noise, Encoding\", \"Receiver, Message, Noise\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2867,6,'Test','When analyzing the effectiveness of different business communication channels, compare the levels of information integrity associated with meetings, emails, and official letters. What factors contribute to the varying degrees of information integrity among these channels, and how do these factors influence the choice of communication in a business context?',0.8,1.2,'Hard','C6-THhBJozXQgi5/N3+rdbxBg','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Meetings\", \"Emails\"]','[\"Meetings\", \"Emails\", \"Official Letters\", \"Phone Calls\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2868,6,'Test','Examine the differences between vertical communication and horizontal communication within an organization. How do these types of communication serve different purposes, and what are the implications of these differences on organizational dynamics and problem-solving?',0.8,1.1,'Hard','C6-vhJV1BHXQ5+Lkewz0czyrw','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Vertical communication involves supervisors and subordinates.\"','[\"Horizontal communication involves colleagues.\", \"Vertical communication involves supervisors and subordinates.\", \"Horizontal communication is less formal.\", \"Vertical communication is faster.\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2869,6,'Test','Investigate the processes of encoding and decoding in business communication. How do these processes impact the clarity of the message being communicated, and what strategies can be implemented to enhance understanding and minimize miscommunication among stakeholders?',0.8,1.1,'Hard','C6-2m3Y69JwSa2n38pZ/mnCZA','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Feedback\", \"Clear Encoding\"]','[\"Feedback\", \"Clear Encoding\", \"Complex Language\", \"Ambiguous Messages\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2870,6,'Test','Categorize the different types of business communication and analyze their effectiveness in various scenarios. How do verbal, written, and non-verbal communication methods complement each other, and what challenges arise when relying on a single type of communication in a business environment?',0.8,1.2,'Hard','C6-6Ud1GJv3QZyWgiGTF9nFAA','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Verbal\", \"Written\"]','[\"Verbal\", \"Written\", \"Non-verbal\", \"Visual\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2871,6,'Test','In a scenario where a company is facing a communication breakdown, decompose the elements of the communication process to identify potential sources of noise. What steps can be taken to address these issues and improve overall communication effectiveness within the organization?',1,3.3,'Very Hard','C6-/9WEh82KRbuWkV8BW9mHfg','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Identify sources of noise.\"','[\"Identify sources of noise.\", \"Increase the number of communication channels.\", \"Limit feedback.\", \"Standardize all communication formats.\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2872,6,'Test','Analyze the role of logical reasoning in business communication. Compare deductive and inductive reasoning methods, and discuss how each can be applied to persuade stakeholders effectively. What are the advantages and disadvantages of each reasoning method in a business context?',0.8,1.6,'Hard','C6-QDMWKfOlRnSTkBreLB+uRg','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Deductive reasoning\", \"Inductive reasoning\"]','[\"Deductive reasoning\", \"Inductive reasoning\", \"Emotional reasoning\", \"Statistical reasoning\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2873,6,'Test','Contrast the characteristics of top-down and bottom-up communication methods in an organization. How do these methods influence decision-making processes and the flow of information? What are the potential benefits and drawbacks of each approach?',0.8,1.6,'Hard','C6-YV0gfDNXSQu7fbisR91PVQ','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Top-down communication includes instructions.\"','[\"Top-down communication includes instructions.\", \"Bottom-up communication involves reports.\", \"Top-down communication is informal.\", \"Bottom-up communication is faster.\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2874,6,'Test','Examine how the choice of communication medium can affect the integrity of information shared within a business context. What are the implications of using emails versus face-to-face meetings, and how can organizations optimize their communication strategies to enhance information integrity?',0.8,1.2,'Hard','C6-1dk/85JvSIiXfxpTkPmSTQ','Multiple Choice - Many','[\"Emails\", \"Face-to-Face Meetings\"]','[\"Emails\", \"Face-to-Face Meetings\", \"Official Letters\", \"Text Messages\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2875,6,'Test','Investigate the importance of feedback in the communication process. How does feedback help in minimizing noise and ensuring that the intended message is received accurately? What strategies can organizations implement to foster a culture of effective feedback?',1,3.6,'Very Hard','C6-dhAK8M07Q3q8ZReDXwPbdA','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Feedback minimizes noise.\"','[\"Feedback minimizes noise.\", \"Feedback complicates communication.\", \"Feedback is only necessary in written communication.\", \"Feedback should be avoided.\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2876,6,'Test','In preparing a presentation, the 3P analysis is crucial for understanding the audience, purpose, and environment. How would you differentiate between the audience\'s interests and the purpose of your presentation when designing your content? Consider how neglecting either aspect could impact the effectiveness of your presentation.',0.8,1.4,'Hard','C6-tDVkFWkXTyetsTlT2zVyEA','Multiple Choice - Single','\"The audience\'s interests should align with the presentation\'s purpose.\"','[\"The audience\'s interests should align with the presentation\'s purpose.\", \"The purpose is more important than the audience\'s interests.\", \"Audience interest is irrelevant to the presentation\'s success.\", \"The purpose and audience interests are always the same.\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2877,6,'Test','In the context of presentation material creation, how do visual factors such as color and font choice contribute to the effectiveness of your message? Examine the relationship between these visual elements and audience perception, considering how they can either enhance or detract from your message.',1,3.6,'Very Hard','C6-yal0L8lLTNKc15l7ashAWA','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Visual factors significantly influence audience perception.\"','[\"Visual factors significantly influence audience perception.\", \"Visual factors are secondary to content.\", \"Color choice does not affect audience engagement.\", \"Font style is irrelevant in presentations.\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2878,6,'Test','In the scenario creation stage of a presentation, what elements must be examined to ensure the scenario effectively communicates the intended message? Decompose the components of a successful scenario and analyze how they interact to support the overall presentation goal.',0.8,1.3,'Hard','C6-ssurPaItQs6XdXabWoTlRw','Multiple Choice - Single','\"The scenario must reflect key points and audience needs.\"','[\"The scenario must reflect key points and audience needs.\", \"The scenario can be vague if the content is strong.\", \"Only the presenter’s style matters, not the scenario.\", \"The scenario should be lengthy to cover all points.\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2879,6,'Test','A project manager is evaluating the effectiveness of the project life cycle stages in a recent software development project. Given the five processes of initiating, planning, executing, monitoring and controlling, and closing, which stage do you believe is most critical for ensuring project success? Justify your choice based on the importance of early planning and risk management as described in the project management methodologies.',1,3.5,'Very Hard','C6-RYmX/5cwQQS3qkGkpbhhmg','Multiple Choice - Single','\"Planning\"','[\"Initiating\", \"Planning\", \"Executing\", \"Closing\"]','2025-03-23 22:08:54','2025-03-23 22:08:54'),(2880,1,'Test','What is the term for user-centered design?',0.2,-3.2,'Very Easy','C1-Uv5/BF/iTe6s1O+8Nx9KBQ','Identification','[\"User-focused design\", \"UCD\"]',NULL,'2025-03-24 06:18:28','2025-03-24 06:18:28'),(2881,1,'Test','List one UI design tool.',0.2,-3.3,'Very Easy','C1-mwbSF0oSSRC7gZB6hF/g4w','Identification','[\"Adobe Photoshop\", \"Photoshop\"]',NULL,'2025-03-24 06:18:28','2025-03-24 06:18:28'),(2882,1,'Test','What do you call the feedback provided to users?',0.2,-3.5,'Very Easy','C1-Djm4qd+6SPmKe5G7FXgCwg','Identification','[\"Meaningful feedback\", \"Feedback\"]',NULL,'2025-03-24 06:18:28','2025-03-24 06:18:28'),(2883,1,'Test','Identify one method for confirming destructive behavior.',0.2,-5,'Very Easy','C1-tc3ccLayRFmuLvpDbXcd4g','Identification','[\"Undo function\", \"Undo\"]',NULL,'2025-03-24 06:18:28','2025-03-24 06:18:28'),(2884,1,'Test','Name one tool for visual analytics.',0.2,-4.1,'Very Easy','C1-LYG9q5MSSk+mndKUbLdBZA','Identification','[\"Google Analytics\", \"GA\"]',NULL,'2025-03-24 06:18:28','2025-03-24 06:18:28'),(2885,1,'Test','In t